# ernoslabs.com — full self-host. Caddy terminates TLS on THIS machine
# (Let's Encrypt, auto-renewed) and hands everything to serve_ernos.py on
# :8899, which serves the site from the working tree plus all the live APIs
# (community, canvas, archive, TTS, project zips). No third party in the path.
#
# bind: the Tailscale system extension permanently reserves wildcard *:443,
# so we bind the LAN address specifically (BSD: specific beats wildcard —
# verified). Caddy therefore runs as a root LaunchDaemon
# (com.ernoslabs.caddy), because macOS only allows unprivileged low-port
# binds on the wildcard. 192.168.1.240 = this Mac's ethernet; keep the DHCP
# reservation on the router pointed at it.
{
	email maria.smith.xo@outlook.com
}

ernoslabs.com {
	bind 192.168.1.240 127.0.0.1
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8899
}

www.ernoslabs.com {
	bind 192.168.1.240 127.0.0.1
	redir https://ernoslabs.com{uri} permanent
}
